----
== Strings -- expansions

* Bash has a LOT of string variable expansions
* They are really useful

# bash:
path=/foo/bar/baz
echo ">>${path#/}<<"
echo ">>${path#/*/}<<"
echo ">>${path##/*}<<"
echo ">>${path%/*}<<"
echo ${#path}
echo ${path//\//=}

# bash:
echo foo.{json,yaml,xml,htm{,l}}
echo mv /some/long/path/file.{text,txt}
